1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,040
Making rice koji starts by soaking rice in water.

2
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:05,280
Hi, I'm Nalase Akouji Maker from Japan.

3
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:08,640
After soaking overnight, dry it well and steam the rice.

4
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:10,720
Don't bore it. You have to steam it.

5
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:14,320
After about 45 minutes, when it's shiny and perfectly steamed,

6
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:15,919
sprinkle Koji's spores on top.

7
00:00:15,919 --> 00:00:18,400
I'm using Tanikouji from Hishio-Ku in Kyoto.

8
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,080
This one is perfect for rice koji.

9
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:23,120
Mixed gently so the spores reach every single grain,

10
00:00:23,120 --> 00:00:25,519
then wrap it in cross to keep it cozy.

11
00:00:25,519 --> 00:00:28,080
To prevent drying, I put it in the container.

12
00:00:28,159 --> 00:00:31,119
This Boston pizza box works surprisingly well.

13
00:00:31,119 --> 00:00:34,960
Now, I'm going to make it at a warm temperature for about 48 hours.

14
00:00:34,960 --> 00:00:37,439
This time, I'm using my DIY incubator.

15
00:00:37,439 --> 00:00:40,000
Check out my other video for how to make it.

16
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
After 24 hours, transfer your baby koji to a bigger container.

17
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,439
Keep it around 30-45-45 degrees Celsius.

18
00:00:47,439 --> 00:00:49,759
It will start to heat up naturally.

19
00:00:49,759 --> 00:00:51,439
Mix it every few hours.

20
00:00:51,439 --> 00:00:54,320
And the last 15 hours, just let it go.

21
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:56,879
Your koji will be ready around 48 hours.

22
00:00:56,960 --> 00:00:58,800
It doesn't have to be super fluffy.

23
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,800
Enjoy the process.
